Firstly, there is a problem in your CSS. `nth-child` is a pseudo selector and not a class. Also, it [doesn&#39;t work in conjunction with classes][1].

You need to use JavaScript to accomplish this. I&#39;m sure the code can be optimised, but I&#39;m leaving that upto you to figure out. These are the steps that I&#39;m following:

 1. Reset the state of all the `li`s on every checkbox click
 2. Add a class called `active` to all visible `li`s
 3. Add a `highlight` class to all even numbered `active` `li`s. The code uses [`:odd`][2] because this custom jQuery selector is 0-indexed

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    $(document).ready(function() {
      $(&#39;.results &gt; li&#39;).hide();

      $(&#39;div.tags&#39;).find(&#39;input:checkbox&#39;).on(&#39;click&#39;, function() {
        $(&#39;.results &gt; li&#39;).hide().removeClass(&#39;highlight active&#39;);

        $(&#39;div.tags&#39;).find(&#39;input:checked&#39;).each(function() {
          $(&#39;.results &gt; li.&#39; + $(this).attr(&#39;rel&#39;)).show().addClass(&#39;active&#39;);
        });

        $(&#39;.active:odd&#39;).addClass(&#39;highlight&#39;)
      });
    });

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .highlight {
      background-color: red;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;tags&quot;&gt;
      &lt;label&gt;
                &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; rel=&quot;arts&quot; /&gt;
                Arts
            &lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;label&gt;
                &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; rel=&quot;computers&quot; /&gt;
                Computers
            &lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;label&gt;
                &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; rel=&quot;health&quot; /&gt;
